# Job Application Tracker

A FastAPI application for tracking job applications with authentication.

## Setup

1. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the application:

bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
Access the API documentation:

Swagger UI: http://localhost:8000/docs


API Usage
Create a user:

bash
POST /users/
{
  "username": "your_username",
  "email": "your_email@example.com",
  "password": "your_password"
}
Get an access token:

bash
POST /token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=your_username&password=your_password
Use the token to access protected endpoints (add to headers):

text
Authorization: Bearer <your_token>
User-Agent: Postman (or any value)
Create a job application:

bash
POST /applications/
{
  "company": "Tech Corp",
  "position": "Software Developer",
  "status": "applied",
  "date_applied": "2023-10-15"
}
Search applications by status:

bash
GET /applications/search?status=applied
text

## How to Run

1. Create the project structure and files as shown above
2. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the application:

bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
Open your browser to http://localhost:8000/docs to see the API documentation

Testing with Postman
First, create a user at POST /users/

Get a token at POST /token (use form-data with username and password)

Use the token in the Authorization header (Bearer token) for all other requests

Make sure to include a User-Agent header with any value